---
import PageLayout from "@/layouts/Base";
import aboutImg from "../assets/Matt.jpg";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
const meta = {
	title: "About",
	description: "All about me Matt - Developer, Streamer, and Nerd from Sheffield",
};
export const prerender = true;
---

<PageLayout meta={meta}>
	<article class="about-page">
		<!-- Header with offset image -->
		<header class="about-header">
			<div class="header-content">
				<h1 class="page-title glitch-text" data-text="ABOUT_">
					<span class="text-accent">//</span> ABOUT_
				</h1>
				<p class="subtitle">
					DEVELOPER // STREAMER // NERD FROM SHEFFIELD
				</p>
			</div>
			<div class="about-image-container">
				<Image
					src={aboutImg}
					height={aboutImg.height}
					width={aboutImg.width}
					alt="A Photo of Matthew Deloughry"
					loading="eager"
					class="about-image"
					transition:name={"profile-image"}
				/>
				<div class="image-offset-border" aria-hidden="true"></div>
			</div>
		</header>

		<!-- Content cards with intentional offset -->
		<div class="content-grid">
			<div class="brutal-card content-card">
				<h2 class="card-title">
					<span class="text-glitch-cyan">&gt;</span> INIT_
				</h2>
				<p>
					Aye up, I'm Matt<span class="strikethrough">hew</span> Peck-Deloughry, a web developer from Sheffield.
					I've been slinging code for nigh on 15 years now and I can tell you, I've developed a reet fondness for it.
				</p>
				<p>
					You'll mostly find me professionally using PHP and Laravel, but I like to have a bit of fun
					with JavaScript, TypeScript, and Deno too. There's nowt I love more than creating a problem
					and then figuring out how to fix it with a bit of code. It's like a reet good puzzle!
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class="brutal-card brutal-card-offset content-card">
				<h2 class="card-title">
					<span class="text-glitch-pink">&gt;</span> EXPERIENCE_
				</h2>
				<p>
					I've worked on all sorts of projects in my time, big and small, and I always approach each one
					with the same level of excitement. I'm always looking to learn new things and improve my
					skills, and I love nothing more than bringing ideas to life through code.
				</p>
				<p>
					But it's not just about the code for me. It's about making things, having a bit of fun, and
					always looking for new challenges.
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class="brutal-card content-card">
				<h2 class="card-title">
					<span class="text-twitch">&gt;</span> STREAM_
				</h2>
				<p>
					Oh, and if you're up for it, you can catch me streaming my coding adventures on Twitch. It's a
					bit of a hoot, if I do say so meself!
				</p>
				<p class="disclaimer">
					<span class="text-accent">[!]</span> DISCLAIMER: Above was generated by AI, asking to write a blurb for
					Sheffield coder and nerd, born and bred!
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class="brutal-card brutal-card-offset content-card">
				<h2 class="card-title">
					<span class="text-glitch-red">&gt;</span> TRUTH_
				</h2>
				<p>
					But really I think this sums me up perfectly, I love the challenge of using some language I
					love to solve something, finding the pit-falls and ways out of those said holes. Finding
					solutions to problems is what it's all about - using all my "hacks" and "lessons" to produce a
					comprehensive solution.
				</p>
				<p>
					I try to share that enthusiasm in everything I do, from mentoring and streaming to just
					chatting with people. When you love what you do, it makes everything more fun and rewarding.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>

		<!-- Motto quote -->
		<blockquote class="motto-block">
			<div class="quote-content">
				<span class="quote-prefix">&gt;&gt;</span>
				<span class="glitch-hover" data-text="Av' fun developing, Av' fun learning, then Av'a crack at engineering it!">
					"Av' fun developing, Av' fun learning, then Av'a crack at engineering it!"
				</span>
			</div>
		</blockquote>
	</article>

	<style>
		.about-page {
			display: flex;
			flex-direction: column;
			gap: 3rem;
		}

		/* Header */
		.about-header {
			display: grid;
			grid-template-columns: 1fr auto;
			gap: 3rem;
			align-items: start;
			padding-bottom: 2rem;
			border-bottom: 4px solid var(--theme-accent);
		}

		.header-content {
			display: flex;
			flex-direction: column;
			gap: 1rem;
		}

		.page-title {
			font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
			font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 8vw, 5rem);
			font-weight: 700;
			line-height: 1;
			margin: 0;
			text-transform: uppercase;
			color: var(--theme-text);
		}

		.subtitle {
			font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
			font-size: 0.875rem;
			color: var(--theme-muted);
			letter-spacing: 0.1em;
			margin: 0;
		}

		/* Image with offset border */
		.about-image-container {
			position: relative;
			width: 280px;
			height: 280px;
			flex-shrink: 0;
		}

		.about-image {
			width: 100%;
			height: 100%;
			object-fit: cover;
			border: 4px solid var(--theme-accent);
			filter: grayscale(100%) contrast(1.1);
			transition: filter 0.3s ease;
		}

		.about-image-container:hover .about-image {
			filter: grayscale(0%) contrast(1);
		}

		.image-offset-border {
			position: absolute;
			top: 8px;
			left: 8px;
			right: -8px;
			bottom: -8px;
			border: 2px solid var(--glitch-cyan);
			pointer-events: none;
		}

		/* Content grid with broken layout */
		.content-grid {
			display: grid;
			grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
			gap: 2rem;
		}

		.content-card {
			padding: 2rem;
		}

		.content-card:nth-child(2) {
			margin-top: 3rem;
		}

		.content-card:nth-child(3) {
			margin-top: -2rem;
		}

		.card-title {
			font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
			font-size: 1.25rem;
			font-weight: 700;
			margin: 0 0 1.5rem 0;
			text-transform: uppercase;
			color: var(--theme-text);
		}

		.content-card p {
			font-size: 1rem;
			line-height: 1.7;
			color: var(--theme-muted);
			margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
		}

		.content-card p:last-child {
			margin-bottom: 0;
		}

		.strikethrough {
			text-decoration: line-through;
			color: var(--glitch-red);
		}

		.disclaimer {
			font-size: 0.875rem !important;
			padding: 0.75rem;
			border: 2px dashed var(--theme-accent);
			background: rgba(218, 255, 1, 0.05);
		}

		.text-glitch-cyan {
			color: var(--glitch-cyan);
		}

		.text-glitch-pink {
			color: var(--glitch-pink);
		}

		.text-glitch-red {
			color: var(--glitch-red);
		}

		/* Motto block */
		.motto-block {
			margin: 2rem 0;
			padding: 2rem;
			border: 4px solid var(--theme-accent);
			background: var(--theme-bg-secondary);
		}

		.quote-content {
			font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
			font-size: clamp(1rem, 2.5vw, 1.5rem);
			color: var(--theme-text);
			display: flex;
			gap: 1rem;
			align-items: flex-start;
		}

		.quote-prefix {
			color: var(--theme-accent);
			flex-shrink: 0;
		}

		/* Responsive */
		@media (max-width: 900px) {
			.about-header {
				grid-template-columns: 1fr;
				text-align: center;
			}

			.about-image-container {
				margin: 0 auto;
				width: 200px;
				height: 200px;
			}

			.content-grid {
				grid-template-columns: 1fr;
			}

			.content-card:nth-child(2),
			.content-card:nth-child(3) {
				margin-top: 0;
			}
		}
	</style>
</PageLayout>
